📘 PROJECT EVALUATION

👉 Project Evaluation ka matlab:
“Project start karne se pehle check karna ki yeh project sahi hai ya nahi”

✔ Check karte hai:
Useful hai ya nahi
Profit milega ya nahi
Risk kitna hai

📌 1. Strategic Assessment

👉 Ye check karta hai:
“Project company ke goals ke saath match karta hai ya nahi”

✔ Questions:
Company ko fayda hoga?
Long-term growth me help karega?
Market me demand hai?
🎯 Example:

Agar company AI product banana chahti hai
aur tum website bana rahe ho → ❌ match nahi

👉 Simple:
“Project company ki strategy ke according hai ya nahi”

📌 2. Technical Assessment

👉 Ye check karta hai:
“Project technically possible hai ya nahi”

✔ Check:
Technology available hai?
Team skilled hai?
Tools sahi hai?
🎯 Example:
AI app banana hai but team ko AI nahi aata → ❌ problem

👉 Simple:
“Hum ye project bana sakte hai ya nahi”

📌 3. Cost Benefit Analysis

👉 Compare karta hai:
“Kitna cost lagega vs kitna benefit milega”

✔ Formula (simple):
Benefit > Cost → ✔ Good project
Cost > Benefit → ❌ Not good

🎯 Example:
Cost = ₹50,000
Benefit = ₹1,50,000 → ✔ profitable

👉 Simple:
“Fayda zyada hai ya kharcha?”

📌 4. Cash Flow Forecasting

👉 Ye batata hai:
“Future me paise kab aayenge aur kab jayenge”

✔ Includes:
Incoming money (Revenue)
Outgoing money (Expenses)
🎯 Example:
Month 1 → -₹20,000 (investment)
Month 3 → +₹50,000 (profit)

👉 Simple:
“Future me paisa flow ka prediction”

📌 5. Cost Benefit Evaluation Techniques

Ye methods use hote hai decision lene ke liye 👇

🔹 1. Payback Period

👉 Kitne time me investment recover hoga

🎯 Example:
Invest ₹1,00,000
Return ₹25,000/year
→ Payback = 4 years

👉 Short payback = ✔ better

🔹 2. Net Present Value (NPV)

👉 Future money ka current value calculate karta hai

👉 Simple:
“Aaj ka paisa future ke paisa se zyada valuable hota hai”

✔ NPV > 0 → ✔ Good project
✔ NPV < 0 → ❌ Reject

🔹 3. Internal Rate of Return (IRR)

👉 Expected profit rate (%) batata hai

✔ Higher IRR → ✔ better project

👉 Simple:
“Kaunsa project zyada profitable hai decide karna”

📌 6. Risk Evaluation

👉 Risk Evaluation ka matlab:
“Project me kya problems aa sakti hai”

✔ Types of Risks:
Technical risk (technology fail)
Financial risk (loss)
Time risk (delay)
Resource risk (team issue)
🎯 Example:
Developer leave ho gaya
Server crash
Budget increase
✔ Risk Handling:
Backup plan
Extra budget
Skilled team

👉 Simple:
“Problems pehle se soch ke ready rehna”

🎯 FINAL SUMMARY (Easy Revision)
Topic	Simple Meaning
